commodities.price
Class Prices

java.lang.Object
  commodities.price.Prices
public class Prices
extends Object

The Prices class contains the prices for a single commoditiy contract for a processing time period. The prices that are containd in the association are the open, high, low, and closing prices for the period. If available, the open interst and volume are also included.

Version:
1.0
Author:
J.R. Titko
Updated:
2004.11.11

Constructor Detail

Prices

public Prices(Date date,
              double open,
              double high,
              double low,
              double close)
Creates a price group with an open, high, low, and close price. Other values are set to 0.

Parameters:
date - The date timestamp that this grouping is for.
open - The opening price for this grouping.
high - The high price for this grouping.
low - The low price for this grouping.
close - The closing price for this grouping.

Prices

public Prices(Date date,
              double open,

              double low,
              double close,
              long volume,

Creates a price group with an open, high, low, and close price in addition to the open interst and volume for the grouping.

Parameters:
date - The date timestamp that this grouping is for.
open - The opening price for this grouping.
high - The high price for this grouping.
low - The low price for this grouping.
close - The closing price for this grouping.
volume - The volumne of trades for this grouping.
